added.title: Twin-Con
added.description: Babs and Buster attend a twin convention but are soon ostracized for not being exactly the same. Hamton accidentally becomes famous, and Plucky steps up as his manager. And Sweetie won't let anything stop her from finishing her board game.

added.title: Give Pizza a Chance
added.description: Rivals Buster and Plucky decide to throw an epic pizza party and are shocked to find out they're actually getting along while Babs and Sweetie get into their first roommate disagreement.

added.title: Snow Country for Old Men
added.description: In an attempt to win the holidays, Chef brings snowmen to life to entertain the kids. But when they turn out to be evil, Chef and the kids have to jingle some bells.

added.title: Snack to the Future
added.description: Owen wants his favorite treat, Jiggle Giggle, so bad that he's willing to use a time machine to get to snacktime quicker. But when he ends up stuck in the past, Owen must decide between getting home and getting fed.

added.title: Trucker Hall of Fame
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to help Muscle Man get to the Big Rig Museum to spread his dad's hat's ashes.

added.title: Out of Commission
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have one last day with the cart before they have to get rid of it.

added.title: Fancy Restaurant
added.description: Muscle Man has to impress his girlfriend's parents at a fancy dinner.

added.title: Diary
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to fix a lock on Margaret's diary before she gets back from a weekend trip.

added.title: The Best VHS in the World
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to return an overdue VHS to the store so they won't be banned from renting new movies.

added.title: Prankless
added.description: The guys want to win a prank war with a rival park.

added.title: Death Bear
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to get a picture in death bear's cage to impress Margaret and Eileen.

added.title: Fuzzy Dice
added.description: Everyone wants to give Pops some fuzzy dice for his birthday.

added.title: Sugar Rush
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to pick up the donuts for the morning meeting.

added.title: Bad Kiss
added.description: Mordecai finally makes his move and tries to kiss Margaret.

added.title: Bug City Frame-Up
added.description: While revisiting Bug CIty, the bears are accused of crimes they didn't commit. Ice Bear must team up with old friend Sam Spider Spade to help prove the bears innocence.

added.title: Don't Fear the Repo
added.description: Repo men, Octagon and Rhomboid Vreedle, have been hired to return Ship to the Upgrade who spawned him. But Ben, Kevin and Gwen have different plans.

added.title: Single Handed
added.description: A bounty hunter is hot on Ben, but when he gets his chance to remove the Omnitrix from Ben's wrist, he sends Ben deep into the Null Void!

added.title: If All Else Fails
added.description: A hibernating Highbreed officer awakens and triggers a device designed to destroy the planet. Now Ben must figure out a way to stop him.

added.title: In Charm's Way
added.description: Kevin is charmed by a beautiful girl and finds himself under her spell (literally) as Charmcaster has returned and is forcing Kevin to do her biding.

added.title: Ghost Town
added.description: Vilgax visits Ghostfreak in prison and gets more than he bargained for when Ghostfreak begins possessing the citizens of Vilgaxia.

added.title: Get in Gear/Free-Wheelin' Ferris Wheel
added.description: Panic erupts in Pretty Big City when the big clock breaks and no one is able to tell what time it is./Zee is showing off his inventions at his rocket-powered show, including his latest creation, a rocket powered Ferris wheel.

added.title: The Great Giggle
added.description: The Care Bears are to witness the annual blooming of the Pinata Tree, an ancient event that can only happen if the Keeper of the Tree sees something that makes him giggle. Good Luck's giggle-inducing entertainment act goes awry because he relies on his errant lucky shamrock for success. He must learn to forgo luck and practice his act instead.

added.title: Time to Try
added.description: At lunch in the park, Mel's friends are unwilling to try a taste of her kimchi. Barney whips up a beach day with Baby Bop, where she doesn't want to do anything new. The kids realize the value of trying new things to show others you care.

added.title: Air-Show Don't Tell
added.description: Batwing and Goldie secretly decide to participate in the Gotham Air-Show, but when Batman needs their help, they must choose between winning the competition and their responsibilities to fight crime.

added.title: The Bestah Way
added.description: When Harley Quinn's Hyena goes missing, Bibi agrees to help Jestah look for her.

added.title: Batty Race
added.description: When the Legion of Zoom plan to cheat their way to winning the Gotham Grand Prix, the Batwheels zoom into action to emsure the race is won the right way, fair and square !

added.title: The Need for Feed/The Zipline Sisters of Treetop Woods
added.description: MacBarm is bringing food to his hungry chickens, that is, until all of the food falls out of his truck./Grandma and her twin sister want to recreate their old zipline act, but quickly discover that the zipline no longer exists!

added.title: Rain, Rain Go Away
added.description: After Grumpy's anger sends his belly badge out of control with a thunderstorm that floods a newly-planted Whiffle meadow, he vows to never be grumpy again. Renaming himself "Mr. Happy," he drives everyone crazy with niceness. When the Whiffles desperately need his clouds to make rain and Mr. Happy can't deliver, Cheer and the team must get him back in touch with his inner grump.

added.title: The Light in the Forest
added.description: Cheer bonds with a migrating firefly-like creature, called a Sparklewing, who stows aboard the Cloudseeker. The two become good friends, but there's a problem: Sparklewings must finish their migration to bring life-giving nutrients to the fields of the Silver Lining. Cheer's difficult and emotional parting with her new friend is only possible once they both accept that it's for a greater good.
